Author: uhhh206
Text: 20 years here.  Fully recovered for over a decade, while I maintained a low-healthy BMI -- stayed in a small weight fluctuation, tracked calories and macros religiously when I gained weight but without going overboard, and seriously thought I was over this shit for good.  ED: lmao bitch you thought

Author: mustyday
Text: Yeah I’ve had EDNOS since I was 19 (I’m 25 now) with periods of “recovery” (weight gain) in between and what the fuck do I have to show for it? I dropped out of my last year of university bc of it and now I’m still fat and unhappy so,,,,,waste of my time
